next: Fix ssc typer bug (busi testbed find): `case class C() extends Trait` is NOT recognized as a subtype of Trait — `def f(): Trait = C()` errors "Type mismatch: expected Trait, found C". Root cause: Typer.scala isCompatible has NO nominal-subtype check; single-uppercase names pass ONLY by accident via looksLikeTypeVar (treated as type vars), multi-char mixed-case names (Ab, Foo, MemoryRepo) correctly fail because no real C<:T check exists. Min repro: `trait Ab:\n def m:Int\ncase class Bc() extends Ab:\n def m:Int=1\ndef f():Ab=Bc()`. Fix: add a classParents Map[String,List[String]] populated from templ.inits in the Defn.Class/Defn.Trait arms (both checkStat ~404/671 and the trait arm ~414/714); in isCompatible add a transitive nominal-subtype check (actual=Named(an), expected=Named(en): true if en reachable from an via classParents). Additive — only turns false-negatives into correct passes. Steps: spec scalascript/specs/typer-nominal-subtype.md; edit Typer.scala; add TyperTest case (both single+multi-char names, transitive trait chain, negative case C NOT extends T still errors); sbt build; run backendInterpreter/test (or targeted typer gate); confirm busi vr-1 trait SPI shape now compiles. Blocks busi vr-1 (owner directive: use traits).
